{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":697,"text":"When I was invited to give this talk \na couple of months ago,"},{"time":5383,"text":"we discussed a number \nof titles with the organizers,"},{"time":8893,"text":"and a lot of different items were \nkicked around and were discussed."},{"time":12308,"text":"But nobody suggested this one,"},{"time":14349,"text":"and the reason for that\nwas two months ago,"},{"time":17278,"text":"Ebola was escalating exponentially"},{"time":20190,"text":"and spreading over wider geographic areas\nthan we had ever seen,"},{"time":24553,"text":"and the world was terrified, \nconcerned and alarmed"},{"time":27822,"text":"by this disease, in a way we've not \nseen in recent history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32790,"text":"But today, I can stand here \nand I can talk to you about beating Ebola"},{"time":38960,"text":"because of people \nwhom you've never heard of,"},{"time":42656,"text":"people like Peter Clement, a Liberian \ndoctor who's working in Lofa County,"},{"time":49815,"text":"a place that many of you have \nnever heard of, probably, in Liberia."},{"time":55294,"text":"The reason that Lofa County \nis so important"},{"time":57684,"text":"is because about five months ago,"},{"time":60115,"text":"when the epidemic was \njust starting to escalate,"},{"time":64533,"text":"Lofa County was right at the center, \nthe epicenter of this epidemic."},{"time":69477,"text":"At that time, MSF\nand the treatment center there,"},{"time":73222,"text":"they were seeing dozens of patients \nevery single day,"},{"time":76097,"text":"and these patients, these communities\nwere becoming more and more terrified"},{"time":80345,"text":"as time went by, with this disease \nand what it was doing to their families,"},{"time":84713,"text":"to their communities, \nto their children, to their relatives."},{"time":88329,"text":"And so Peter Clement was charged with \ndriving that 12-hour-long rough road"},{"time":93092,"text":"from Monrovia, the capital,\nup to Lofa County,"},{"time":97339,"text":"to try and help bring control\nto the escalating epidemic there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101701,"text":"And what Peter found when he arrived was\nthe terror that I just mentioned to you."},{"time":107063,"text":"So he sat down with the local chiefs, \nand he listened."},{"time":111304,"text":"And what he heard was heartbreaking."},{"time":114945,"text":"He heard about the devastation \nand the desperation"},{"time":119279,"text":"of people affected by this disease."},{"time":122578,"text":"He heard the heartbreaking stories"},{"time":124656,"text":"about not just the damage\nthat Ebola did to people,"},{"time":128103,"text":"but what it did to families \nand what it did to communities."},{"time":132589,"text":"And he listened to the local chiefs there\nand what they told him --"},{"time":136999,"text":"They said, \"When our children are sick, \nwhen our children are dying,"},{"time":140443,"text":"we can't hold them at a time when \nwe want to be closest to them."},{"time":144247,"text":"When our relatives die, we can't take care\nof them as our tradition demands."},{"time":148937,"text":"We are not allowed to wash \nthe bodies to bury them"},{"time":151617,"text":"the way our communities and \nour rituals demand."},{"time":154801,"text":"And for this reason, they were\ndeeply disturbed, deeply alarmed"},{"time":158208,"text":"and the entire epidemic \nwas unraveling in front of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161995,"text":"People were turning on the healthcare \nworkers who had come,"},{"time":164911,"text":"the heroes who had come to try \nand help save the community,"},{"time":168265,"text":"to help work with the community,\nand they were unable to access them."},{"time":173184,"text":"And what happened then was \nPeter explained to the leaders."},{"time":178402,"text":"The leaders listened. \nThey turned the tables."},{"time":181137,"text":"And Peter explained what Ebola was.\nHe explained what the disease was."},{"time":184744,"text":"He explained what it did\nto their communities."},{"time":187019,"text":"And he explained that Ebola threatened \neverything that made us human."},{"time":192177,"text":"Ebola means you can't hold your children\nthe way you would in this situation."},{"time":196563,"text":"You can't bury your dead \nthe way that you would."},{"time":198873,"text":"You have to trust these people \nin these space suits to do that for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203516,"text":"And ladies and gentlemen, what \nhappened then was rather extraordinary:"},{"time":206865,"text":"The community and the health workers, \nPeter, they sat down together"},{"time":210111,"text":"and they put together a new plan \nfor controlling Ebola in Lofa County."},{"time":215168,"text":"And the reason that this is such \nan important story, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":219642,"text":"is because today, this county, which is \nright at the center of this epidemic"},{"time":224736,"text":"you've been watching, \nyou've been seeing in the newspapers,"},{"time":227563,"text":"you've been seeing on \nthe television screens,"},{"time":231306,"text":"today Lofa County is nearly eight weeks\nwithout seeing a single case of Ebola."},{"time":237393,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244449,"text":"Now, this doesn't mean that \nthe job is done, obviously."},{"time":247872,"text":"There's still a huge risk\nthat there will be additional cases there."},{"time":251128,"text":"But what it does teach us \nis that Ebola can be beaten."},{"time":254392,"text":"That's the key thing."},{"time":256049,"text":"Even on this scale,"},{"time":257216,"text":"even with the rapid kind of growth\nthat we saw in this environment here,"},{"time":261113,"text":"we now know Ebola can be beaten."},{"time":264571,"text":"When communities come together \nwith health care workers, work together,"},{"time":268562,"text":"that's when this disease can be stopped."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271235,"text":"But how did Ebola end up\nin Lofa County in the first place?"},{"time":274885,"text":"Well, for that, we have to go back \n12 months, to the start of this epidemic."},{"time":279577,"text":"And as many of you know, \nthis virus went undetected,"},{"time":282828,"text":"it evaded detection for three \nor four months when it began."},{"time":286803,"text":"That's because this is not \na disease of West Africa,"},{"time":289466,"text":"it's a disease of Central Africa, \nhalf a continent away."},{"time":292611,"text":"People hadn't seen the disease before;"},{"time":294547,"text":"health workers hadn't seen \nthe disease before."},{"time":297156,"text":"They didn't know what \nthey were dealing with,"},{"time":299324,"text":"and to make it \neven more complicated,"},{"time":301383,"text":"the virus itself was causing a symptom,\na type of a presentation"},{"time":305951,"text":"that wasn't classical of the disease."},{"time":308216,"text":"So people didn't even recognize \nthe disease, people who knew Ebola."},{"time":312631,"text":"For that reason it evaded detection \nfor some time,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":316490,"text":"But contrary to public belief \nsometimes these days,"},{"time":319660,"text":"once the virus was detected, \nthere was a rapid surge in of support."},{"time":325175,"text":"MSF rapidly set up an Ebola treatment \ncenter, as many of you know, in the area."},{"time":330236,"text":"The World Health Organization\nand the partners that it works with"},{"time":333330,"text":"deployed eventually hundreds of people \nover the next two months"},{"time":337005,"text":"to be able to help track the virus."},{"time":339393,"text":"The problem, ladies and gentlemen,\nis by then, this virus,"},{"time":343424,"text":"well known now as Ebola, \nhad spread too far."},{"time":346977,"text":"It had already outstripped what was \none of the largest responses"},{"time":350186,"text":"that had been mounted so far\nto an Ebola outbreak."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353995,"text":"By the middle of the year,\nnot just Guinea"},{"time":356403,"text":"but now Sierra Leone and Liberia\nwere also infected."},{"time":360366,"text":"As the virus was spreading geographically,\nthe numbers were increasing"},{"time":365233,"text":"and at this time, not only were \nhundreds of people infected"},{"time":370289,"text":"and dying of the disease,"},{"time":372168,"text":"but as importantly,\nthe front line responders,"},{"time":374907,"text":"the people who had gone to try and help,"},{"time":377750,"text":"the health care workers, the other \nresponders"},{"time":380892,"text":"were also sick and dying by the dozens."},{"time":383934,"text":"The presidents of these countries \nrecognized the emergencies."},{"time":386882,"text":"They met right around that time, \nthey agreed on common action"},{"time":390422,"text":"and they put together an emergency \njoint operation center in Conakry"},{"time":394640,"text":"to try and work together to finish this\ndisease and get it stopped,"},{"time":398960,"text":"to implement the strategies\nwe talked about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402242,"text":"But what happened then was something \nwe had never seen before with Ebola."},{"time":406199,"text":"What happened then was the virus, \nor someone sick with the virus,"},{"time":409785,"text":"boarded an airplane, \nflew to another country,"},{"time":413181,"text":"and for the first time,\nwe saw in another distant country"},{"time":417323,"text":"the virus pop up again."},{"time":419879,"text":"This time it was in Nigeria,\nin the teeming metropolis of Lagos,"},{"time":424286,"text":"21 million people."},{"time":426245,"text":"Now the virus was in that environment."},{"time":429228,"text":"And as you can anticipate, \nthere was international alarm,"},{"time":432768,"text":"international concern on a scale that \nwe hadn't seen in recent years"},{"time":436536,"text":"caused by a disease like this."},{"time":438990,"text":"The World Health Organization immediately \ncalled together an expert panel,"},{"time":443630,"text":"looked at the situation, \ndeclared an international emergency."},{"time":447256,"text":"And in doing so, the expectation would be\nthat there would be a huge outpouring"},{"time":452346,"text":"of international assistance\nto help these countries"},{"time":455316,"text":"which were in so much trouble\nand concern at that time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459364,"text":"But what we saw was \nsomething very different."},{"time":462341,"text":"There was some great response."},{"time":465869,"text":"A number of countries came to assist --\nmany, many NGOs and others, as you know,"},{"time":470630,"text":"but at the same time, the opposite \nhappened in many places."},{"time":474046,"text":"Alarm escalated, and very soon \nthese countries found themselves"},{"time":478161,"text":"not receiving the support they needed,\nbut increasingly isolated."},{"time":482556,"text":"What we saw was commercial airlines\n[stopped] flying into these countries"},{"time":487290,"text":"and people who hadn't even been\nexposed to the virus"},{"time":489881,"text":"were no longer allowed to travel."},{"time":492043,"text":"This caused not only problems, obviously, \nfor the countries themselves,"},{"time":495971,"text":"but also for the response."},{"time":498093,"text":"Those organizations that were \ntrying to bring people in,"},{"time":501055,"text":"to try and help them\nrespond to the outbreak,"},{"time":503261,"text":"they could not get \npeople on airplanes,"},{"time":505193,"text":"they could not get them into the \ncountries to be able to respond."},{"time":508392,"text":"In that situation,\nladies and gentleman,"},{"time":510404,"text":"a virus like Ebola takes advantage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513639,"text":"And what we saw then was something \nalso we hadn't seen before."},{"time":518577,"text":"Not only did this virus \ncontinue in the places"},{"time":521733,"text":"where they'd already become infected,\nbut then it started to escalate"},{"time":525324,"text":"and we saw the case numbers\nthat you see here,"},{"time":527692,"text":"something we'd never seen before\non such a scale,"},{"time":530746,"text":"an exponential increase of Ebola cases"},{"time":533783,"text":"not just in these countries or the areas \nalready infected in these countries"},{"time":538024,"text":"but also spreading further and \ndeeper into these countries."},{"time":541883,"text":"Ladies and gentleman,\nthis was one of the most concerning"},{"time":544947,"text":"international emergencies in public health\nwe've ever seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550502,"text":"And what happened in these countries then,"},{"time":552553,"text":"many of you saw, again, on the television,\nread about in the newspapers,"},{"time":556742,"text":"we saw the health system start to collapse\nunder the weight of this epidemic."},{"time":562102,"text":"We saw the schools begin to close, \nmarkets no longer started,"},{"time":566722,"text":"no longer functioned the way \nthat they should in these countries."},{"time":570042,"text":"We saw that misinformation and \nmisperceptions started to spread"},{"time":574161,"text":"even faster through the communities,\nwhich became even more alarmed"},{"time":577645,"text":"about the situation."},{"time":579260,"text":"They started to recoil from those people \nthat you saw in those space suits,"},{"time":582844,"text":"as they call them, \nwho had come to help them."},{"time":585091,"text":"And then the situation\ndeteriorated even further."},{"time":588118,"text":"The countries had to declare\na state of emergency."},{"time":590800,"text":"Large populations needed to be quarantined\nin some areas, and then riots broke out."},{"time":596205,"text":"It was a very, very terrifying situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599975,"text":"Around the world,\nmany people began to ask,"},{"time":602834,"text":"can we ever stop Ebola \nwhen it starts to spread like this?"},{"time":606803,"text":"And they started to ask, how well \ndo we really know this virus?"},{"time":611585,"text":"The reality is we don't know \nEbola extremely well."},{"time":614740,"text":"It's a relatively modern disease\nin terms of what we know about it."},{"time":618735,"text":"We've known the disease only for 40 years,"},{"time":621020,"text":"since it first popped up\nin Central Africa in 1976."},{"time":624502,"text":"But despite that, we do know many things:"},{"time":627582,"text":"We know that this virus\nprobably survives in a type of a bat."},{"time":631805,"text":"We know that it probably enters \na human population"},{"time":634921,"text":"when we come in contact with a wild animal"},{"time":637528,"text":"that has been infected with the virus \nand probably sickened by it."},{"time":641086,"text":"Then we know that the virus\nspreads from person to person"},{"time":644307,"text":"through contaminated body fluids."},{"time":646580,"text":"And as you've all seen,"},{"time":648071,"text":"we know the horrific disease\nthat it then causes in humans,"},{"time":651553,"text":"where we see this disease cause\nsevere fevers, diarrhea, vomiting,"},{"time":656071,"text":"and then unfortunately, in 70 percent\nof the cases or often more, death."},{"time":662541,"text":"This is a very dangerous,\ndebilitating, and deadly disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668344,"text":"But despite the fact that we've not known\nthis disease for a particularly long time,"},{"time":672517,"text":"and we don't know everything about it,\nwe do know how to stop this disease."},{"time":677394,"text":"There are four things\nthat are critical to stopping Ebola."},{"time":680608,"text":"First and foremost, the communities \nhave got to understand this disease,"},{"time":684922,"text":"they've got to understand \nhow it spreads and how to stop it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688443,"text":"And then we've got to be able to have \nsystems that can find every single case,"},{"time":692519,"text":"every contact of those cases,"},{"time":694525,"text":"and begin to track the transmission chains\nso that you can stop transmission."},{"time":698682,"text":"We have to have treatment centers,\nspecialized Ebola treatment centers,"},{"time":702304,"text":"where the workers can be protected"},{"time":704817,"text":"as they try to provide support\nto the people who are infected,"},{"time":709689,"text":"so that they might survive the disease."},{"time":712134,"text":"And then for those who do die,"},{"time":714334,"text":"we have to ensure there is a safe, but at\nthe same time dignified, burial process,"},{"time":720192,"text":"so that there is no spread \nat that time as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724798,"text":"So we do know how to stop Ebola, and these\nstrategies work, ladies and gentlemen."},{"time":729299,"text":"The virus was stopped in Nigeria \nby these four strategies"},{"time":733458,"text":"and the people implementing \nthem, obviously."},{"time":735562,"text":"It was stopped in Senegal, where it had\nspread, and also in the other countries"},{"time":739584,"text":"that were affected by this virus, \nin this outbreak."},{"time":743177,"text":"So there's no question that \nthese strategies actually work."},{"time":747018,"text":"The big question, ladies and gentlemen,\nwas whether these strategies could work"},{"time":752326,"text":"on this scale, in this situation,\nwith so many countries affected"},{"time":756600,"text":"with the kind of exponential \ngrowth that you saw."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760206,"text":"That was the big question that we were \nfacing just two or three months ago."},{"time":764757,"text":"Today we know the answer to that question."},{"time":768801,"text":"And we know that answer \nbecause of the extraordinary work"},{"time":771779,"text":"of an incredible group of NGOs,\nof governments, of local leaders,"},{"time":776546,"text":"of U.N. agencies and many humanitarian \nand other organizations"},{"time":780932,"text":"that came and joined the fight\nto try and stop Ebola in West Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784850,"text":"But what had to be done there \nwas slightly different."},{"time":788293,"text":"These countries took those strategies \nI just showed you;"},{"time":791218,"text":"the community engagement,\nthe case finding, contact tracing, etc.,"},{"time":796624,"text":"and they turned them on their head."},{"time":798548,"text":"There was so much disease,\nthey approached it differently."},{"time":801481,"text":"What they decided to do was they would \nfirst try and slow down this epidemic"},{"time":806912,"text":"by rapidly building as many beds as\npossible in specialized treatment centers"},{"time":811899,"text":"so that they could prevent the disease\nfrom spreading from those were infected."},{"time":817203,"text":"They would rapidly build out\nmany, many burial teams"},{"time":819652,"text":"so that they could safely\ndeal with the dead,"},{"time":821827,"text":"and with that, they would try \nand slow this outbreak"},{"time":824394,"text":"to see if it could actually then \nbe controlled using the classic approach"},{"time":828613,"text":"of case finding and contact tracing."},{"time":831364,"text":"And when I went to West Africa\nabout three months ago,"},{"time":834657,"text":"when I was there\nwhat I saw was extraordinary."},{"time":837669,"text":"I saw presidents opening emergency\noperation centers themselves against Ebola"},{"time":842595,"text":"so that they could personally coordinate \nand oversee and champion"},{"time":846363,"text":"this surge of international support \nto try and stop this disease."},{"time":850450,"text":"We saw militaries from within \nthose countries and from far beyond"},{"time":854001,"text":"coming in to help build \nEbola treatment centers"},{"time":856741,"text":"that could be used to isolate \nthose who were sick."},{"time":859991,"text":"We saw the Red Cross movement working with\nits partner agencies on the ground there"},{"time":864417,"text":"to help train the communities so that\nthey could actually safely bury their dead"},{"time":869574,"text":"in a dignified manner themselves."},{"time":872132,"text":"And we saw the U.N. agencies, \nthe World Food Program,"},{"time":874933,"text":"build a tremendous air bridge"},{"time":876834,"text":"that could get responders to every single\ncorner of these countries rapidly"},{"time":880736,"text":"to be able to implement the strategies\nthat we just talked about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884089,"text":"What we saw, ladies and gentlemen, \nwhich was probably most impressive,"},{"time":887434,"text":"was this incredible work\nby the governments,"},{"time":890451,"text":"by the leaders in these countries,\nwith the communities,"},{"time":893468,"text":"to try to ensure people \nunderstood this disease,"},{"time":896486,"text":"understood the extraordinary things they \nwould have to do to try and stop Ebola."},{"time":902169,"text":"And as a result, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":904462,"text":"we saw something that we did not know\nonly two or three months earlier,"},{"time":908905,"text":"whether or not it would be possible."},{"time":911179,"text":"What we saw was \nwhat you see now in this graph,"},{"time":914309,"text":"when we took stock on December 1."},{"time":917118,"text":"What we saw was we could \nbend that curve, so to speak,"},{"time":920560,"text":"change this exponential growth,"},{"time":922934,"text":"and bring some hope back\nto the ability to control this outbreak."},{"time":927163,"text":"And for this reason, ladies and gentlemen,\nthere's absolutely no question now"},{"time":931217,"text":"that we can catch up with this outbreak \nin West Africa and we can beat Ebola."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937785,"text":"The big question, though, \nthat many people are asking,"},{"time":940958,"text":"even when they saw this curve, they said,"},{"time":942941,"text":"\"Well, hang on a minute --\nthat's great you can slow it down,"},{"time":945845,"text":"but can you actually\ndrive it down to zero?\""},{"time":947896,"text":"We already answered that question \nback at the beginning of this talk,"},{"time":951437,"text":"when I spoke about Lofa County in Liberia."},{"time":955590,"text":"We told you the story\nhow Lofa County got to a situation"},{"time":959016,"text":"where they have not seen\nEbola for eight weeks."},{"time":961829,"text":"But there are similar stories from \nthe other countries as well."},{"time":965205,"text":"From Gueckedou in Guinea,"},{"time":967451,"text":"the first area where the first case was\nactually diagnosed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971959,"text":"We've seen very, very few cases\nin the last couple of months,"},{"time":975373,"text":"and here in Kenema, in Sierra Leone, \nanother area in the epicenter,"},{"time":979800,"text":"we have not seen the virus\nfor more than a couple of weeks --"},{"time":983061,"text":"way too early to declare \nvictory, obviously,"},{"time":986156,"text":"but evidence, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":987931,"text":"not only can the response \ncatch up to the disease,"},{"time":991556,"text":"but this disease can be driven to zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994722,"text":"The challenge now, of course, \nis doing this on the scale needed"},{"time":998878,"text":"right across these three countries,\nand that is a huge challenge."},{"time":1004244,"text":"Because when you've been at something\nfor this long, on this scale,"},{"time":1008949,"text":"two other big threats \ncome in to join the virus."},{"time":1012949,"text":"The first of those is complacency,"},{"time":1016052,"text":"the risk that as this \ndisease curve starts to bend,"},{"time":1019475,"text":"the media look elsewhere, \nthe world looks elsewhere."},{"time":1022739,"text":"Complacency always a risk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024371,"text":"And the other risk, of course, is when\nyou've been working so hard for so long,"},{"time":1028714,"text":"and slept so few hours \nover the past months,"},{"time":1032352,"text":"people are tired, people become fatigued,"},{"time":1034590,"text":"and these new risks \nstart to creep into the response."},{"time":1038660,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, I can tell you today\nI've just come back from West Africa."},{"time":1042940,"text":"The people of these countries,\nthe leaders of these countries,"},{"time":1046640,"text":"they are not complacent."},{"time":1048136,"text":"They want to drive Ebola to zero \nin their countries."},{"time":1051879,"text":"And these people, yes, they're tired, \nbut they are not fatigued."},{"time":1055664,"text":"They have an energy, they have a courage,"},{"time":1057869,"text":"they have the strength \nto get this finished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060399,"text":"What they need, ladies\nand gentlemen, at this point,"},{"time":1063153,"text":"is the unwavering support of the \ninternational community,"},{"time":1066781,"text":"to stand with them,"},{"time":1068189,"text":"to bolster and bring even more support \nat this time, to get the job finished."},{"time":1073047,"text":"Because finishing Ebola right now \nmeans turning the tables on this virus,"},{"time":1078082,"text":"and beginning to hunt it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079817,"text":"Remember, this virus, this whole crisis, \nrather, started with one case,"},{"time":1085004,"text":"and is going to finish with one case."},{"time":1087703,"text":"But it will only finish if those countries\nhave got enough epidemiologists,"},{"time":1092027,"text":"enough health workers, enough logisticians\nand enough other people working with them"},{"time":1096644,"text":"to be able to find every one \nof those cases, track their contacts"},{"time":1100126,"text":"and make sure that this disease \nstops once and for all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1104220,"text":"Ladies and gentleman, Ebola can be beaten."},{"time":1107557,"text":"Now we need you to take this story out\nto tell it to the people who will listen"},{"time":1112245,"text":"and educate them \non what it means to beat Ebola,"},{"time":1115457,"text":"and more importantly,\nwe need you to advocate with the people"},{"time":1119189,"text":"who can help us bring the resources we\nneed to these countries,"},{"time":1122743,"text":"to beat this disease."},{"time":1124517,"text":"There are a lot of people out there \nwho will survive and will thrive,"},{"time":1128699,"text":"in part because of what you do \nto help us beat Ebola."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1132101,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1133587,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}